PLUGINS                                                          *wort-plugins*

Plugins are managed via native |vim.pack|. Run `:PackList` to see installed
packages or `:PackPicker` to browse with Telescope.

Commands~

  :PackList                                                        *:PackList*
                        List all installed packages
  :PackPicker                                                    *:PackPicker*
                        Browse packages with Telescope
  :PackStatus                                                    *:PackStatus*
                        Show package count
  :PackUpdate                                                    *:PackUpdate*
                        Update all packages
  :PackAdd {url}                                                    *:PackAdd*
                        Add a package by URL
  :PackDel {name}                                                   *:PackDel*
                        Delete a package by name

==============================================================================
LSP                                                                  *wort-lsp*

Language servers are configured in `lua/lsp/servers/`. Each server only
activates if its executable is found in PATH.

Commands~

  :LspHealth                                                      *:LspHealth*
                        Check installation status of all configured servers

Adding a new server~

  1. Add Mason package name to `ensure_installed` in `lua/plugins/mason.lua`
  2. Create `lua/lsp/servers/{name}.lua` with config structure
  3. Restart Neovim

Server config structure:
>lua
  return {
      name = "server_name",
      cmd = "executable",
      config = {
          cmd = { "executable", "args" },
          filetypes = { "filetype" },
          root_markers = { ".git" },
      }
  }
<

